    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9600 AND 9700 SLEEPER AND NON-SLEEPER CABS -
        SHEET METAL REPAIRS - PLUG WELD WINDSHIELD FENCE (EDGE)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="1">
        <title>PLUG WELD WINDSHIELD FENCE (EDGE)</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean the area around each plug weld hole to bare metal.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use clamps to assure good contact between panels being joined.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use chill block behind inner panel to prevent blistering on back side of metal and to
                protect inside trim from weld heat or flame.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Plug weld at each hole (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600671">Figure 71</hotlnk>) until all welds are complete. Mig Welder with 3/64 inch
                (1.19mm) Diameter Spec. No. 4043 Weld Wire is recommended.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1600671" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1600671" filename="../figg16/G1600671.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 71. Plug Welding Windshield Fence</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CLAMP</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CHILL BLOCK</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. PLUG WELD</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Make a good weld with base metal and use caution to avoid burning through.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
